# Protected Files

NEVER modify these files without explicit approval:

- `packages/excalidraw/data/restore.ts` — file format backward compatibility
- `packages/excalidraw/actions/manager.ts` — core action system dispatcher
- `packages/excalidraw/types.ts` — core type definitions (AppState, ExcalidrawElement)
- `packages/element/src/types.ts` — element type union and interfaces
- `packages/excalidraw/editor-jotai.ts` — Jotai state isolation setup
- `packages/excalidraw/renderer/staticScene.ts` — main canvas rendering pipeline
- `packages/excalidraw/renderer/interactiveScene.ts` — interactive layer rendering

## Why these files are protected
- `restore.ts`: Ensures backward compatibility with all saved `.excalidraw` files. Breaking changes here corrupt user data.
- `manager.ts`: Core dispatcher — all 100+ actions depend on it.
- `types.ts`: Changing core types cascades across the entire codebase.
- Renderers: Direct canvas manipulation — subtle bugs are hard to detect.

## If you MUST change a protected file
1. Understand all dependencies (grep for imports of this file)
2. Run the complete test suite: `yarn test`
3. Run full build: `yarn build`
4. Document the change rationale

## How to verify
- Protected files should not appear in git diff without explicit approval
- Run `git diff --name-only` and check against this list
